"""Slopsquid statistical AI-overuse patterns.

Source: sam-paech/slop-score (MIT license)
Methodology: 67-LLM statistical comparison against human writing.
Filtered: only patterns with ZERO occurrences in 384K words of human prose.

Bigrams: 122 AI-only two-word phrases (e.g. "voice low", "eyes widened")
Trigrams: 416 AI-only three-word phrases (e.g. "voice barely whisper", "took deep breath")

Word-level patterns are NOT included — human prose uses slopsquid words at
higher density (38.4/5K) than the pipeline (26.9/5K), making them useless
as discriminators. The signal is entirely in multi-word collocations.

Cap: 0 (zero tolerance). These patterns literally never appear in published
human prose. Any occurrence is a strong AI signal.
"""

